attachments.title: Available Pantheon Platform Commands
attachments.text:
Actions default to all sites, unless --siteName provided
Passing --siteName=site1,site2 will limit reports and actions to given sites.
Actions can be appended to chain commands and results into one execution

attachments.title: Actions can be chained together optionally into a Job, and results reported back to user.

reportOutdated: Emit report to Slack channel of Pantheon sites with outdated upstreams
siteNames: If provided to Pantheon Jobrunner, will scan only sites given.  Default behavior, load all site details for actions
createMultidev:
Creates multiDev environment for all sites, can be limited with use of --siteName
Default multidev environment name is "patching" unless --environment argument is given to jobrunner
applyUpdates:
Applies upstream updates to a sites patching multiDev environment
Multidev environment will be created if necessary
If --environment argument is given, updates are applied to given name
performBackup:
Creates backup of all environments of sites
If --environment given then backups are performed only to request site.environment
environment:
Restricts any action to a sites environments to only environments given as argument
Example: performBackup
